Hi, I'd like to be able to pretty print both instances as well as classes using the `__rich_console__` protocol (specifically in the context of pydantic models). In theory this can be achieved using [Descriptors](https://docs.python.org/3/howto/descriptor.html), like so:

``` python
class RichConsole:
    def __get__(self, ins, cls):
        if ins is None:
            return cls.__cls_rich_console__

        return ins.__inst_rich_console__


